[1889 in poetry|1889]])\n*Date unknown:\n** [[Alexander McLachlan (poet)|Alexander McLachlan]], [[Scottish poetry|Scottish]]-born [[Canadian poetry|Canadian]] poet (died [[1896 in poetry|1896]])\n** [[Charlotta \u00d6berg]], [[Swedish poetry|Swedish]] poet (died [[1856 in poetry|1856]])\n\n==Deaths==\nBirth years link to the corresponding \"[year] in poetry\" article:\n* May 14 or 16 \u2013 [[Matthew Lewis (writer)|Matthew Lewis]], [[English poetry|English]] Gothic writer (born [[1775 in poetry|1775]])\n* November 23 \u2013 [[John Williams (satirist)|John Williams]], [[English poetry|English]] satirist, journalist and poet, in the United States (born [[1761 in poetry|1716]])\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|Poetry}}\n* [[Poetry]]\n* [[List of years in poetry]]\n* [[List of years in literature]]\n* [[19th century in literature]]\n* [[19th century in poetry]]\n* [[Romantic poetry]]\n* [[Golden Age of Russian Poetry]] (1800\u20131850)\n* [[Weimar Classicism]] period in [[German poetry|Germany]], commonly considered to have begun in 1788 and to have ended either in 1805, with the death of [[Friedrich Schiller]], or 1832, with the death of [[Johann von Goethe|Goethe]]\n* [[List of poets]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Poetry of different cultures and languages}}\n{{Lists of poets}}\n\n[[Category:1818|Poetry]]\n[[Category:1818 poems|*]]\n[[Category:19th-century poetry]]\n", "name_user": "Camboxer", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eJohn Keats:location clarified", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1818_in_poetry"}
